        <ol class="fs-5">
          <li>
            <strong>Gentle Stretching:</strong> Ease cramps by gently stretching the affected muscle.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Warm Compress:</strong> Apply a warm cloth or heating pad to relax tense muscles.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Hydration and Electrolytes:</strong> Drink water and consider natural electrolyte-rich drinks.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Herbal Teas:</strong> Consume ginger or chamomile tea to help reduce inflammation and soothe aches.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Massage:</strong> Gently massage the cramped area to improve blood flow and relax the muscle.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <h3 class="fw-bold mt-4 mb-3">What Not To Do:</h3>
        <ul class="fs-5">
          <li>Do not overexert the affected muscle further.</li>
